Pre-heat your #grill{} to medium–high. Marinate the @British chicken thighs{6} by mixing them with the @Chinese five spice{1}, @salt{1/4%tsp}, a good grind of @black pepper{} and @oil{1%tbsp}. Leave to marinate while you chop the veggies.

Chop the tops and bottoms off the @carrots{2} and then peel them. Cut in half lengthways and then with the flat side on the board, cut the carrots into half moon shapes, roughly ½cm thick. Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel, remove the ends and slice thinly into half moon shapes. Remove the root and dark green parts from the @leek{1} and discard. Chop the rest of the leek into ½cm slices. Chop the root from the @spring greens{1}(sliced) and separate the leaves. Roughly chop the leaves into 2cm wide strips.

Peel both the @garlic cloves{2} and @ginger{1%piece} then grate them on the fine side of your #grater{}. Tear the leaves from the @coriander{10} and chop the stalks as finely as you can. Keep the leaves whole.

Heat a #saucepan{} over medium heat and add @oil{1%tbsp}. Add the carrots, onions and leeks to the pan and cook for ~{5%minutes} or until they begin to soften, stirring frequently to prevent them from burning. Stir in the garlic, ginger, @cinnamon stick{1} and chopped coriander. Cook for another ~{1%minute} and pour in @water{1.5%l}. Bring to the boil, add in the @chicken stock pots{2} and reduce the heat to low. Leave your broth to bubble away on low heat for ~{15%minutes} while you grill the chicken.

Place the chicken thighs on a #baking tray{} under your grill and cook for ~{15%minutes}. After ~{7%minutes}, turn the chicken thighs over and cook for a further ~{7-8%minutes} or until the flesh is no longer pink. Once your chicken is cooked, slice it into thin strips roughly ½cm thick.

Whilst the chicken is cooking, zest and squeeze the juice from the @lime{1}. Check the vegetables in your broth are soft and cooked through and stir in your spring greens. Cook for ~{3%minutes} or until they have wilted. Stir in the @udon noodles{300} and warm through. Season with the @soy sauce{1%tbsp}, and the juice and zest of your lime.

Spoon your broth into deep #bowls{}, making sure everyone gets a fair share of the noodles and top with your sliced chicken. Garnish with the coriander leaves and slurp away!

> Before HelloFresh it seems that our Chef André was QUITE the jet-setter. It was just before he got on Tokyo's famous bullet train, that he had the steaming chicken ramen that inspired this dish.